org.ptolemy.ptango.lib.webSocket

Class WebSocketEndpointManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ptolemy.ptango.lib.webSocket.WebSocketEndpointManager

  • public class WebSocketEndpointManager
extends java.lang.Object
    A singleton class that manages websocket endpoints and their connection openers (clients, servlets).
    Since:
    Ptolemy II 11.0
    Author:
    Elizabeth Latronico
    Pt.AcceptedRating:

    Pt.ProposedRating:
    Red (ltrnc)

      • closeServlets

        public void closeServlets()
        Close all servlet websocket endpoints. Called by webserver in wrapup(). Synchronized to avoid interleaving opening and closing endpoints.

      • getServlet

        public PtolemyWebSocketServlet getServlet(java.lang.String path)
                                   throws IllegalActionException
        Get the servlet for the given path. If the servlet does not exist, create it. Called by the web server. Synchronized to avoid interleaving creating and deleting a servlet.
        Parameters:
        path - The URI the servlet should be mapped to.
        Returns:
        The servlet mapped to this path.
        Throws:
        IllegalActionException - Not thrown in this base class.

      • openLocalServices

        public void openLocalServices(java.util.HashSet<WebSocketService> services,
                              int portNumber)
                       throws IllegalActionException
        Open connections for the given set of services by looking up each service's affiliated endpoint and opening a connection for that endpoint. Assumes that these are local services. The WebServer uses this to open local services after it has started. Synchronized so that subscribing and unsubscribing are not interleaved.
        Parameters:
        services - The set of services to open connections for.
        portNumber - The port number of the local web server.
        Throws:
        IllegalActionException - If one or more services cannot be opened.

      • pathToURI

        public static java.net.URI pathToURI(java.lang.String path)
                              throws IllegalActionException
        Check the given path to see if it is a valid websocket URI and return a URI. Throw an exception if the path is invalid.
        Parameters:
        path - The string representation of a websocket URI.
        Returns:
        The URI corresponding to this path string.
        Throws:
        IllegalActionException - If the path is not a valid URI.

      • subscribe

        public void subscribe(WebSocketService service,
                      java.lang.String path)
               throws IllegalActionException
        Add the given service as a subscriber to the endpoint for this path. Create a new endpoint if none exists for this path. Synchronized to avoid interleaved subscribing and unsubscribing. Generally, subscribers should subscribe in initialize() and should unsubscribe in wrapup().
        Parameters:
        service - The service to add as a subscriber.
        path - The URL to subscribe to.
        Throws:
        IllegalActionException - If the URI is not valid.
        See Also:
        unsubscribe(WebSocketService, String)

      • unsubscribe

        public void unsubscribe(WebSocketService service,
                        java.lang.String path)
        Remove the given service as a subscriber to the endpoint for this path. Delete the endpoint if no services are associated with it. Synchronized to avoid conflicting writes to tables.
        Parameters:
        service - The service to remove as a subscriber
        path - The URL to subscribe to
        See Also:
        subscribe(WebSocketService, String)
